pr_body:
### Description

This is a  draft pull request for the `pick_ik` tutorial in the MoveIt tutorials. The content mainly depends on the information from the readme file in `pick_ik` [repo](https://github.com/PickNikRobotics/pick_ik/blob/main/README.md). I tried to make it more beginner-friendly.

The tutorial contents are as follows:

Introduction about `pick_ik`:

Provides an overview of pick_ik as a customizable IK solver, highlights its key features, and how it works.

Installation Section:

Explains options for binary installation and building from source.

Usage Section:

Adds an example of configuring the `kinematics.yaml` file to use `pick_ik` as a kinematics plugin in MoveIt.

Parameter Description:

Highlights key parameters and their explanations to help beginners start configuring `pick_ik` to use with MoveIt.
___

Please let me know your feedback to improve the tutorial content. I would be glad to consider further refinements to make it most beneficial. 

Thank you!

### Checklist
- [x] **Required by CI**: Code is auto formatted using [clang-format](http://moveit.ros.org/documentation/contributing/code)
- [x] While waiting for someone to review your request, please consider reviewing [another open pull request](https://github.com/ros-planning/moveit2/pulls) to support the maintainers
